  m_Name: Ternary Operator
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  title: Ternary Operator
  textDataArray:
  - "<size=45>Short Hand If...Else (Ternary Operator)\r</size>\nThere is also a short-hand
    if else, which is known as the <color=black>ternary</color> operator because
    it consists of three operands. It can be used to replace multiple lines of code
    with a single line. It is often used to replace simple if else statements:\n\n<size=45>Syntax</size>\r\nvariable
    = (condition) <#F2B84B>?</color> expressionTrue <#F2B84B>:</color>  expressionFalse;\n\n"
  - "Instead of writing:\n\n<size=45>Example</size>\r\n\n<color=black>C# Equivalent:</color>\nint
    time = 20;\r\nif (time < 18) \r\n{\r\n  Console.WriteLine(\"Good day.\");\r\n}
    \r\nelse \r\n{\r\n  Console.WriteLine(\"Good evening.\");\r\n}"
  - "<color=black>C# Adventures Equivalent:</color>\nint time = 20;\r\nif (time <
    18) \r\n{\r\n  hero.Say(\"Good day.\");\r\n} \r\nelse \r\n{\r\n  hero.Say(\"Good
    evening.\");\r\n}\n"
  - 'You can simply write:


    <size=45>Example</size>


    <color=black>C# Equivalent</color>

    int
    time = 20;

    string result = (time < 18) ? "Good day." : "Good evening.";

    Console.WriteLine(result);


    <color=black>C#
    Adventures Equivalent</color>

    int time = 20;

    string result = (time
    < 18) ? "Good day." : "Good evening.";

    hero.Say(result);'
